finding: convert loadUser callback → async/await; preserve order + single error mapping.

invariants:
- order: missing_id → db.findUser → not_found → audit.log → cache.set
- db_err routes `next(err)` (single mapping)
- no change to callback signature of loadUser (still `(req,res,next)`)
- no new trust on headers
- session.userId authoritative; `x-user-id` not trusted

skeleton:
```
async function loadUser(req, res, next) {
  try {
    const id = req.session?.userId;
    if (!id) return next(err_401);           // missing_id → 401
    let user;
    try {
      user = await findUserAsync(id);        // db.findUser
    } catch (e) {
      return next(e);                        // db_err → next(err)
    }
    if (!user) return next(err_404);         // not_found
    await auditLog(...);                      // audit.log
    await cacheSet(...);                      // cache.set
    req.user = user;
    next();
  } catch (e) {
    next(e);                                 // single error mapping
  }
}
```

notes:
- promisify `db.findUser` once; do not change its signature elsewhere
- watch `this` binding on `db.findUser` → bind if method-style
- keep `next(err)` as only failure path
- do not swallow audit.log / cache.set errors silently unless prior behavior did

verification:
- test: missing session → `401` via `next(err)`
- test: db.findUser rejects → `next(err)` fires once, no double-next
- test: user null → not_found path

